{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2d040fc-08f3-4851-afe4-39bebe12f232","content":"The fix works — 0 tests discovered but `dotnet test` now exits with **code 0** instead of 8.\n\n### Summary\n\nMTP exit code 8 = \"no tests found,\" which VSTest didn't flag. The fix is the MSBuild property:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>0</TestingPlatformExitCodeOnNoTests>\n```\n\n**Alternative (CI-level fix):** If you'd rather not change the project, set the environment variable in your pipeline:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE: 8\n```\n\nBoth approaches restore the VSTest behavior of treating zero-test assemblies as success.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a73860e3-f5d6-4543-b64f-d07e6e6fbb15","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"0BC7:1A4FD7:49B6D6:55E8B1:69F005C5"},"id":"5824aed3-0c23-419f-a545-bd22852e6f62","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:56:50.565Z","parentId":"86c06629-02ac-4da3-9aec-c84700e635d1"}
